President Biden held a press conference in the Roosevelt Room, where he discussed the federal response to Hurricane Ida and the ongoing recovery efforts in Maui, Hawaii. He mentioned that he had spoken with several governors who were impacted by the storm and approved an early request for emergency declaration in Florida. He highlighted the importance of remaining vigilant and providing support to the affected states. The President also emphasized the impact of the climate crisis and the need to invest in infrastructure to withstand extreme weather events. He announced that $95 million from the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law would be allocated to Hawaii for grid hardening measures. He assured the people of Maui that the federal government would be with them every step of the way in the recovery process. The President also addressed questions about emergency funding, potential power outages, and government shutdown concerns. He expressed his intention to reach out to Senator Mitch McConnell regarding his health.